solved, posts, courses, followers\n\n* Course & roadmap progress\n\n* Badges & streaks\n\n* Mock interview score history\n\n\n\n✅ A self-improvement and portfolio tracker.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 🔟 **Customer Support Ticket System**\n\n\n\n* All users can submit support tickets\n\n* Categories: Bug, Billing, Feature Request, General\n\n* Support execs handle tickets with status flow: Open → Assigned → Resolved\n\n* Admin can:\n\n\n\n* Assign or escalate\n\n* View logs\n\n* Create support staff\n\n* Track ticket resolution time\n\n\n\n✅ Helps maintain support quality & satisfaction.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 🔒 **Admin Control Panel**\n\n\n\n* Manage all users (create, ban, suspend, delete)\n\n* View user logs & ticket history\n\n* Manage courses, tests, and support agents\n\n* Moderate posts/comments\n\n* Assign support roles\n\n* Access analytics of platform usage\n\n\n\n✅ Centralized power to run the entire platform.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 💳 **Subscription Management System**\n\n\n\n* Free + Paid (Pro, Mentor) tiers\n\n* Razorpay/Stripe integration\n\n* Limit advanced features based on plan:\n\n\n\n* AI mock interviews\n\n* Video calls\n\n* Premium roadmaps\n\n* Admin can:\n\n\n\n* Create/update/delete plans\n\n* View subscriptions\n\n* Cancel/refund\n\n\n\n✅ Ensures monetization & scaling opportunity.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n## 🧠 **Tech Stack Suggestion**\n\n\n\n| Layer | Tool |\n\n| ------------ | --------------------------------------------- |\n\n| Frontend | React.js, Tailwind CSS, React Native (Mobile) |\n\n| Backend | Node.js, Express.js |\n\n| DB | MongoDB (Mongoose) |\n\n| Auth | JWT, bcrypt, Google OAuth |\n\n| Realtime | Socket.IO, WebRTC |\n\n| AI | OpenAI GPT-4 / Gemini / Whisper / ElevenLabs |\n\n| File Storage | Cloudinary |\n\n| Email | SendGrid / Nodemailer |\n\n| Payments | Stripe / Razorpay |\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n## 🧪 Suggested MVP Timeline (8 Weeks)\n\n\n\n| Week | Feature Set |\n\n| ---- | ------------------------------------------- |\n\n| 1 | Auth system + roles + dashboards (basic UI) |\n\n| 2 | Roadmap module + course progress |\n\n| 3 | Coding practice + question rendering |\n\n| 4 | AI interview module |\n\n| 5 | Chat system + voice call (WebRTC) |\n\n| 6 | Post/comment system + user profile |\n\n| 7 | Test system + admin & support roles |\n\n| 8 | Subscription, analytics, and final polish |\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n## 🌟 Future Enhancements\n\n\n\n* Resume Analyzer\n\n* Group study rooms\n\n* Peer mock interview matchmaking\n\n* College onboarding system (B2B)\n\n* AI-based custom roadmap generator\n\n* App marketplace (for mentors to sell content)\n\n\n\n---\"\"\"),\n            ],\n        ),\n        types.Content(\n            role=\"model\",\n            parts=[\n                types.Part.from_text(text=\"\"\"**Exploring Avatar UI**\n\nI've initiated searches to understand the key design elements and best practices for AI avatar-led interview pages. My focus is now narrowing on UI/UX principles, aiming to synthesize information to build a solid foundational understanding of how to make these pages intuitive and engaging. I'm prioritizing user-friendly interaction design.\n\n\n**Investigating Interactive AI Design**\n\nI'm now expanding my research to encompass technologies for audio-to-audio and text-to-speech functionalities, focusing on low-latency implementation for seamless interaction.  I'll also be investigating UI/UX patterns for real-time feedback during mock interviews, ensuring it's helpful without being distracting. I'm excited to start examining existing AI-powered interview platforms to identify successful design strategies.\n\n\n**Refining Design Details**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on UI micro-interactions and visual design elements to craft a compelling experience. The initial broad sweep is done; now it's about making the interaction flow seamless. I'm focusing on crafting intuitive feedback mechanisms and visualizing the AI companion's responses. I aim to create a design that’s both visually engaging and practically useful for mock interviews.\n\n\n**Analyzing UI Micro-Interactions**\n\nI've gathered insights on UI/UX best practices, now focusing on fine-tuning the interaction flow for the AI companion.  I'm exploring specific micro-interactions and visual cues to enhance the user's perception of the AI, including how to convey AI sentiment and interview stage progression effectively.  I'm also researching ways to minimize cognitive load while presenting real-time feedback.\n\n\n\"\"\"),\n                types.Part.from_text(text=\"\"\"An intuitive and engaging AI Companion interview page is crucial for PrepMate's success. This design focuses on creating a human-like, interactive experience using a conversational AI avatar, live audio, and real-time feedback. The goal is to make the user feel comfortable and supported while providing actionable insights to improve their interview skills.\n\n### **1. The User Interface: A Blend of Professionalism and Personality**\n\nThe interface is designed to be clean, modern, and easy to navigate, minimizing distractions and allowing the user to focus on the interview.\n\n**Key UI Elements:**\n\n*   **AI Avatar:** A friendly and professional 3D avatar will be the centerpiece of the interaction. It will have subtle animations like blinking, nodding, and gesturing to appear more lifelike. Users can choose from a diverse set of avatars to personalize their experience.\n*   **Conversation Window:** A real-time transcript of the conversation will be displayed, allowing users to review the dialogue as it happens.\n*   **Feedback Panel:** This non-intrusive panel will provide real-time feedback on key metrics.\n*   **Controls:** Simple and intuitive controls will allow the user to start, pause, and end the interview.\n\n### **2. The Core Interaction: Seamless Audio and Lifelike Conversation**\n\nThe primary mode of interaction will be voice, creating a natural and immersive mock interview experience.\n\n**Live Audio-to-Audio:**\n\n*   **Technology:** Leveraging advanced speech recognition and text-to-speech technologies, the platform will enable a seamless, low-latency conversation.\n*   **Natural Language Processing (NLP):** The AI will be powered by a sophisticated NLP model, allowing it to understand and respond to the user's answers in a conversational and contextually relevant manner.\n\n**Native Text-to-Speech:** The AI's voice will be generated using a high-quality, native text-to-speech engine, offering a range of natural-sounding voices that users can select from.\n\n### **3. Real-Time Feedback: Your Personal Interview Coach**\n\nTo provide immediate and actionable insights, the platform will offer real-time feedback on various aspects of the user's performance.\n\n**Key Feedback Metrics:**\n\n*   **Fluency and Pace:** A visual indicator will show the user's speaking rate, helping them maintain a clear and steady pace.\n*   **Filler Word Usage:** The system will detect and highlight the use of filler words like \\\"um,\\\" \\\"ah,\\\" and \\\"like,\\\" helping users become more aware of these habits.\n*   **Sentiment Analysis:** The AI will analyze the user's tone and provide feedback on their perceived confidence and enthusiasm.\n*   **Keyword Match:** For technical interviews, the system can track the use of relevant keywords and concepts.\n\n### **4. Post-Interview Analysis: A Deep Dive into Your Performance**\n\nAfter the interview, users will receive a comprehensive report summarizing their performance and providing detailed feedback.\n\n**Components of the Post-Interview Report:**\n\n*   **Overall Score:** A summary score based on various performance metrics.\n*   **Detailed Breakdown:** In-depth analysis of each question, including the user's answer, the AI's feedback, and suggestions for improvement.\n*   **Actionable Recommendations:** Concrete tips and resources to help users improve in specific areas.\n*   **Full Transcript and Recording:** Users can review the full transcript and listen to the audio recording of their interview to self-assess their performance.\n\n### **5. The Onboarding Experience: Setting the Stage for Success**\n\nA brief and interactive onboarding process will introduce users to the AI Companion and the platform's features. This will include a short tutorial on how to interact with the avatar and understand the real-time feedback. This helps to set clear expectations and ensures a smooth user experience from the very beginning.\"\"\"),\n            ],\n        ),\n        types.Content(\n            role=\"user\",\n            parts=[\n                types.Part.from_text(text=\"\"\"INSERT_INPUT_HERE\"\"\"),\n            ],\n        ),\n    ]\n    tools = [\n        types.Tool(googleSearch=types.GoogleSearch(\n        )),\n    ]\n    generate_content_config = types.GenerateContentConfig(\n        thinking_config = types.ThinkingConfig(\n            thinking_budget=-1,\n        ),\n        tools=tools,\n    )\n\n    for chunk in client.models.generate_content_stream(\n        model=model,\n        contents=contents,\n        config=generate_content_config,\n    ):\n        print(chunk.text, end=\"\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    generate()`) is longer than the maximum allowed length (5000).","path":"message","type":"maxlength","value":"# To run this code you need to install the following dependencies:\n# pip install google-genai\n\nimport base64\nimport os\nfrom google import genai\nfrom google.genai import types\n\n\ndef generate():\n    client = genai.Client(\n        api_key=os.environ.get(\"GEMINI_API_KEY\"),\n    )\n\n    model = \"gemini-2.5-pro\"\n    contents = [\n        types.Content(\n            role=\"user\",\n            parts=[\n                types.Part.from_text(text=\"\"\"Design the AI Companion interview page that will have a AI avatar/character that will act more like real human and interact with real user and use live audio to audio and native text to speech\n\n\n\n\n# 🚀 **PrepMate MVP – Full Project Brief**\n\n\n\nPrepMate is a **role-based, AI-powered platform** designed to help students, job seekers, and educators with interview preparation, communication skills, coding mastery, and collaborative learning — all while providing a rich social and support experience.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n## 🎯 **Core Objective**\n\n\n\nTo provide a **personalized and interactive experience** through AI mock interviews, dynamic roadmaps, coding practice, real-time communication, and support — backed by a modular admin and role system.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n## 🧱 **Core Modules (MVP Breakdown)**\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 1️⃣ **Authentication & Role-Based Access**\n\n\n\n* Email + Password login\n\n* Google OAuth\n\n* Roles: Student, HR, Teacher, Support Executive, Admin\n\n* JWT-based secure session handling\n\n* Email verification & password reset\n\n\n\n✅ Enables differentiated dashboards, permissions, and visibility.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 2️⃣ **Dashboard (Role-Specific)**\n\n\n\n#### 👤 Student Dashboard\n\n\n\n* Roadmap & course progress\n\n* Mock interview feedback\n\n* Practice & test performance\n\n* Activity stats & streaks\n\n\n\n#### 👩‍🏫 Teacher / HR Dashboard\n\n\n\n* Test creation & assignment\n\n* Track student performance\n\n* View submissions & feedback\n\n\n\n#### 👨‍💼 Admin Dashboard\n\n\n\n* Manage users, roles, content\n\n* Moderate posts/tickets/tests\n\n* View logs, create plans, suspend users\n\n\n\n#### 🧑‍💻 Support Executive Dashboard\n\n\n\n* Manage assigned tickets\n\n* Respond to users\n\n* Update ticket statuses\n\n\n\n✅ Ensures personalized and functional workspace for every user type.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 3️⃣ **Roadmap Learning System**\n\n\n\n* Multiple roadmaps: DSA, System Design, Web Dev, etc.\n\n* Each category has:\n\n\n\n* Subtopics (e.g., “Sliding Window”)\n\n* AI explanation\n\n* Practice questions (linked from LeetCode, etc.)\n\n* YouTube video suggestions\n\n* Completion tracking\n\n\n\n✅ Personalized learning journey with AI assistance.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 4️⃣ **AI-Powered Mock Interviews**\n\n\n\n* Text or voice-based mock interviews\n\n* HR-style questions\n\n* AI feedback on:\n\n\n\n* Fluency\n\n* Grammar\n\n* Confidence\n\n* Communication\n\n* Voice-to-Text using Whisper\n\n* Voice output using ElevenLabs / Google TTS\n\n\n\n✅ Builds confidence through realistic HR simulations.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 5️⃣ **Coding Practice Center**\n\n\n\n* Company-wise + topic-wise question bank\n\n* Practice questions from platforms like LeetCode, GFG, HackerRank\n\n* Daily question, bookmarks, filters\n\n\n\n✅ Helps track problem-solving progress aligned with company expectations.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 6️⃣ **Social Community Features**\n\n\n\n* Post feed: text, links, code snippets\n\n* Comment & like system\n\n* Follow/unfollow users\n\n* Share questions in posts\n\n\n\n✅ Encourages peer learning and interaction.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 7️⃣ **1-on-1 Chat & Calls**\n\n\n\n* Real-time text chat (Socket.IO or Firebase)\n\n* Voice & video calls (WebRTC)\n\n* Share questions, files, and resources\n\n* Seen, typing indicators\n\n\n\n✅ Promotes instant help, collaboration, and soft skill practice.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 8️⃣ **Test System (Teacher/HR Tools)**\n\n\n\n* Create coding, MCQ, HR or mixed tests\n\n* Assign to specific users or batches\n\n* Deadline + auto-evaluation\n\n* Students view assigned tests, attempt & get scores\n\n\n\n✅ Enables structured assessments and mentor tracking.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 9️⃣ **User Profile with Analytics**\n\n\n\n* Public & private profiles\n\n* Stats: questions solved, posts, courses, followers\n\n* Course & roadmap progress\n\n* Badges & streaks\n\n* Mock interview score history\n\n\n\n✅ A self-improvement and portfolio tracker.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 🔟 **Customer Support Ticket System**\n\n\n\n* All users can submit support tickets\n\n* Categories: Bug, Billing, Feature Request, General\n\n* Support execs handle tickets with status flow: Open → Assigned → Resolved\n\n* Admin can:\n\n\n\n* Assign or escalate\n\n* View logs\n\n* Create support staff\n\n* Track ticket resolution time\n\n\n\n✅ Helps maintain support quality & satisfaction.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 🔒 **Admin Control Panel**\n\n\n\n* Manage all users (create, ban, suspend, delete)\n\n* View user logs & ticket history\n\n* Manage courses, tests, and support agents\n\n* Moderate posts/comments\n\n* Assign support roles\n\n* Access analytics of platform usage\n\n\n\n✅ Centralized power to run the entire platform.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n### 💳 **Subscription Management System**\n\n\n\n* Free + Paid (Pro, Mentor) tiers\n\n* Razorpay/Stripe integration\n\n* Limit advanced features based on plan:\n\n\n\n* AI mock interviews\n\n* Video calls\n\n* Premium roadmaps\n\n* Admin can:\n\n\n\n* Create/update/delete plans\n\n* View subscriptions\n\n* Cancel/refund\n\n\n\n✅ Ensures monetization & scaling opportunity.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n## 🧠 **Tech Stack Suggestion**\n\n\n\n| Layer | Tool |\n\n| ------------ | --------------------------------------------- |\n\n| Frontend | React.js, Tailwind CSS, React Native (Mobile) |\n\n| Backend | Node.js, Express.js |\n\n| DB | MongoDB (Mongoose) |\n\n| Auth | JWT, bcrypt, Google OAuth |\n\n| Realtime | Socket.IO, WebRTC |\n\n| AI | OpenAI GPT-4 / Gemini / Whisper / ElevenLabs |\n\n| File Storage | Cloudinary |\n\n| Email | SendGrid / Nodemailer |\n\n| Payments | Stripe / Razorpay |\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n## 🧪 Suggested MVP Timeline (8 Weeks)\n\n\n\n| Week | Feature Set |\n\n| ---- | ------------------------------------------- |\n\n| 1 | Auth system + roles + dashboards (basic UI) |\n\n| 2 | Roadmap module + course progress |\n\n| 3 | Coding practice + question rendering |\n\n| 4 | AI interview module |\n\n| 5 | Chat system + voice call (WebRTC) |\n\n| 6 | Post/comment system + user profile |\n\n| 7 | Test system + admin & support roles |\n\n| 8 | Subscription, analytics, and final polish |\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n## 🌟 Future Enhancements\n\n\n\n* Resume Analyzer\n\n* Group study rooms\n\n* Peer mock interview matchmaking\n\n* College onboarding system (B2B)\n\n* AI-based custom roadmap generator\n\n* App marketplace (for mentors to sell content)\n\n\n\n---\"\"\"),\n            ],\n        ),\n        types.Content(\n            role=\"model\",\n            parts=[\n                types.Part.from_text(text=\"\"\"**Exploring Avatar UI**\n\nI've initiated searches to understand the key design elements and best practices for AI avatar-led interview pages. My focus is now narrowing on UI/UX principles, aiming to synthesize information to build a solid foundational understanding of how to make these pages intuitive and engaging. I'm prioritizing user-friendly interaction design.\n\n\n**Investigating Interactive AI Design**\n\nI'm now expanding my research to encompass technologies for audio-to-audio and text-to-speech functionalities, focusing on low-latency implementation for seamless interaction.  I'll also be investigating UI/UX patterns for real-time feedback during mock interviews, ensuring it's helpful without being distracting. I'm excited to start examining existing AI-powered interview platforms to identify successful design strategies.\n\n\n**Refining Design Details**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on UI micro-interactions and visual design elements to craft a compelling experience. The initial broad sweep is done; now it's about making the interaction flow seamless. I'm focusing on crafting intuitive feedback mechanisms and visualizing the AI companion's responses. I aim to create a design that’s both visually engaging and practically useful for mock interviews.\n\n\n**Analyzing UI Micro-Interactions**\n\nI've gathered insights on UI/UX best practices, now focusing on fine-tuning the interaction flow for the AI companion.  I'm exploring specific micro-interactions and visual cues to enhance the user's perception of the AI, including how to convey AI sentiment and interview stage progression effectively.  I'm also researching ways to minimize cognitive load while presenting real-time feedback.\n\n\n\"\"\"),\n                types.Part.from_text(text=\"\"\"An intuitive and engaging AI Companion interview page is crucial for PrepMate's success. This design focuses on creating a human-like, interactive experience using a conversational AI avatar, live audio, and real-time feedback. The goal is to make the user feel comfortable and supported while providing actionable insights to improve their interview skills.\n\n### **1. The User Interface: A Blend of Professionalism and Personality**\n\nThe interface is designed to be clean, modern, and easy to navigate, minimizing distractions and allowing the user to focus on the interview.\n\n**Key UI Elements:**\n\n*   **AI Avatar:** A friendly and professional 3D avatar will be the centerpiece of the interaction. It will have subtle animations like blinking, nodding, and gesturing to appear more lifelike. Users can choose from a diverse set of avatars to personalize their experience.\n*   **Conversation Window:** A real-time transcript of the conversation will be displayed, allowing users to review the dialogue as it happens.\n*   **Feedback Panel:** This non-intrusive panel will provide real-time feedback on key metrics.\n*   **Controls:** Simple and intuitive controls will allow the user to start, pause, and end the interview.\n\n### **2. The Core Interaction: Seamless Audio and Lifelike Conversation**\n\nThe primary mode of interaction will be voice, creating a natural and immersive mock interview experience.\n\n**Live Audio-to-Audio:**\n\n*   **Technology:** Leveraging advanced speech recognition and text-to-speech technologies, the platform will enable a seamless, low-latency conversation.\n*   **Natural Language Processing (NLP):** The AI will be powered by a sophisticated NLP model, allowing it to understand and respond to the user's answers in a conversational and contextually relevant manner.\n\n**Native Text-to-Speech:** The AI's voice will be generated using a high-quality, native text-to-speech engine, offering a range of natural-sounding voices that users can select from.\n\n### **3. Real-Time Feedback: Your Personal Interview Coach**\n\nTo provide immediate and actionable insights, the platform will offer real-time feedback on various aspects of the user's performance.\n\n**Key Feedback Metrics:**\n\n*   **Fluency and Pace:** A visual indicator will show the user's speaking rate, helping them maintain a clear and steady pace.\n*   **Filler Word Usage:** The system will detect and highlight the use of filler words like \\\"um,\\\" \\\"ah,\\\" and \\\"like,\\\" helping users become more aware of these habits.\n*   **Sentiment Analysis:** The AI will analyze the user's tone and provide feedback on their perceived confidence and enthusiasm.\n*   **Keyword Match:** For technical interviews, the system can track the use of relevant keywords and concepts.\n\n### **4. Post-Interview Analysis: A Deep Dive into Your Performance**\n\nAfter the interview, users will receive a comprehensive report summarizing their performance and providing detailed feedback.\n\n**Components of the Post-Interview Report:**\n\n*   **Overall Score:** A summary score based on various performance metrics.\n*   **Detailed Breakdown:** In-depth analysis of each question, including the user's answer, the AI's feedback, and suggestions for improvement.\n*   **Actionable Recommendations:** Concrete tips and resources to help users improve in specific areas.\n*   **Full Transcript and Recording:** Users can review the full transcript and listen to the audio recording of their interview to self-assess their performance.\n\n### **5. The Onboarding Experience: Setting the Stage for Success**\n\nA brief and interactive onboarding process will introduce users to the AI Companion and the platform's features. This will include a short tutorial on how to interact with the avatar and understand the real-time feedback. This helps to set clear expectations and ensures a smooth user experience from the very beginning.\"\"\"),\n            ],\n        ),\n        types.Content(\n            role=\"user\",\n            parts=[\n                types.Part.from_text(text=\"\"\"INSERT_INPUT_HERE\"\"\"),\n            ],\n        ),\n    ]\n    tools = [\n        types.Tool(googleSearch=types.GoogleSearch(\n        )),\n    ]\n    generate_content_config = types.GenerateContentConfig(\n        thinking_config = types.ThinkingConfig(\n            thinking_budget=-1,\n        ),\n        tools=tools,\n    )\n\n    for chunk in client.models.generate_content_stream(\n        model=model,\n        contents=contents,\n        config=generate_content_config,\n    ):\n        print(chunk.text, end=\"\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    generate()"},"value":"# To run this code you need to install the following dependencies:\n# pip install google-genai\n\nimport base64\nimport os\nfrom google import genai\nfrom google.genai import types\n\n\ndef generate():\n    client = genai.Client(\n        api_key=os.environ.get(\"GEMINI_API_KEY\"),\n    )\n\n    model = \"gemini-2.5-pro\"\n    contents = [\n        types.Content(\n            role=\"user\",\n            parts=[\n                types.Part.from_text(text=\"\"\"Design the AI Companion interview page that will have a AI avatar/character that will act more like real human and interact with real user and use live audio to audio and native text to speech\n\n\n\n\n# 🚀 **PrepMate MVP – Full Project Brief**\n\n\n\nPrepMate is a **role-based, AI-powered platform** designed to help students, job seekers, and educators with interview preparation, communication skills, coding mastery, and collaborative learning — all while providing a rich social and support experience.\n\n\n\n---\n\n\n\n## 🎯 **Core Objective**\n\n\n\nTo provide a **personalized and interactive experience** through AI mock interviews, dynamic roadmaps, coding practice, real-time communication, and support — backed by a modular